<li id="cite_note-64"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLockwoodClaus_Fr.C3.B6hlich">Lockwood, Mike; Claus Fröhlich. "<a href="http://www.pubs.royalsoc.ac.uk/media/proceedings_a/rspa20071880.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.pubs.royalsoc.ac.uk/media/proceedings_a/rspa20071880.pdf" rel="nofollow">Recent oppositely directed trends in solar climate forcings and the global mean surface air temperature</a>" (PDF). <i>Proceedings of the Royal Society A</i> <b>463</b>: 2447. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1098%2Frspa.2007.1880" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1098%2Frspa.2007.1880" rel="nofollow">10.1098/rspa.2007.1880</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.pubs.royalsoc.ac.uk/media/proceedings_a/rspa20071880.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.pubs.royalsoc.ac.uk/media/proceedings_a/rspa20071880.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.pubs.royalsoc.ac.uk/media/proceedings_a/rspa20071880.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-07-21</span>.  "Our results show that the observed rapid rise in global mean temperatures seen after 1985 cannot be ascribed to solar variability,whichever of the mechanisms is invoked and no matter how much the solar variation is amplified.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Recent+oppositely+directed+trends+in+solar+climate+forcings+and+the+global+mean+surface+air+temperature&amp;rft.jtitle=Proceedings+of+the+Royal+Society+A&amp;rft.aulast=Lockwood&amp;rft.aufirst=Mike&amp;rft.au=Lockwood%2C+Mike&amp;rft.au=Claus+Fr%C3%B6hlich&amp;rft.volume=463&amp;rft.pages=2447&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1098%2Frspa.2007.1880&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pubs.royalsoc.ac.uk%2Fmedia%2Fproceedings_a%2Frspa20071880.p